On May 26, 2021, the President signed into law H.R. 941, also known as the TRANSPLANT Act of 2021. This act reauthorizes stem cell programs and aims to provide access to needed therapies. Representatives Doris Matsui, Gus Bilirakis, and Chellie Pingree, as well as Senators Jack Reed, Richard Burr, Tina Smith, Tim Scott, and Tammy Duckworth, were acknowledged for their contributions to this legislation.